dialog = PackedStringArray("Mr. McMoneyPants\nHow did you get past the security bot?! You shouldn\'t be here!\nMr. McMoneyPants and Mr. Manager?!", "Mr. Manager\nSir, I might have accidentally left the robot override remote back in the lab, I deeply apologize for that.\nWHAT IS THAT THING BEHIND YOU?!", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nUgh, you idiot. Why do you always bungle everything up when I ask you to do something?\nUm, can I ask what the heck is happening?!", "Mr. Manager\nI\'m sorry sir, I\'ll be better next time.\nWHAT IS GOING ON?! STOP IGNORING ME!", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nUgh, fine, I\'ll answer your questions you little snot. That \"thing\" behind you is the last specimen of a rare tree from the underworld.\n...", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nWe found it in the ruins of the lost prehistoric city of Ri\'leghgoth. We constructed this lab and then transported the specimen here for study.\nBut, why?!", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nThe tree has very specific conditions that it has to grow in - it derives a lot of its power from uncut grass and is immune from damage as long as long as there\'s enough uncut lawn nearby.\nOkay... interesting.", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nHowever, it has answers to some of the greatest secrets of the world - and also great market potential. Its secretions make excellent high powered weedkiller that we are working to bring to market very soon.\n... Okay?", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nYou see, I\'m looking to break into the lawn care business and if I can beat Weed-Be-Gone (tm), then I\'ll dominate the market and create so much shareholder value!\nIs the tree the source of the magical disturbance?!", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nYes, our experiments have indicated that bringing an eldritch underworld tree so close to the surface world has caused some negative side effects to the local ecosystem.\n...", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nBut, the potential shareholder value makes this worth it! Some disagree - I\'m still trying to track down and eliminate that witch that\'s been sticking her nose into our business.\nBut you\'ll destroy the neighborhood!", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nMaybe, I suppose it would suck to lose one of my dozen or so mansions but the world will recover. We\'ve extracted almost all the value we could from this tree anyway.\n...", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nWho cares about a neighborhood anyway when billions of dollars of shareholder value are on the line. Besides, the local weeds becoming more aggressive will drive demand for our product!\nWait, what even is your plan?!", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nThis tree will soon cause a magical collapse that will probably destroy the local neighborhood and cause a weed apocalypse across the country, but...\n...", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nWith our new weed killer available though, people can fight back and I\'ll be a hero! I\'ll make billions and then maybe even become popular enough to win the presidency!\nYou\'re evil!", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nMaybe. But at least I\'ll be rich and powerful. Now that I\'ve done the obligatory \"evil guy explains the master plan\" I suppose this is the part where I let you go.\nWhat? You\'re just, letting me go?", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nHa! I\'m just kidding. Like I would let you leak this to the press. Mr. Manager, kill the child.\nWHAT?!", "Mr. Manager\nSir, I don\'t think I can... That\'s a bit too far for me.\n...", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nThat\'s it, you\'ve failed and defied me for the last time! \n*presses button on a remote*\n...", "Mr. McMoneyPants\nIt\'s a shame I had trigger the self destruct sequence for him. Oh well, I have many more spare clones anyway. Looks like I\'ll have to do the dirty work myself. I\'m finishing what I started and you\'re not stopping me!\nGo stop Mr. McMoneyPants\'s evil plan!")
time_limit = 0.0
